The paper focuses on learning blind image quality assessment models, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of pairwise learning-to-rank algorithms also suggests a potential fit for machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of large-scale databases and the focus on automatic data collection and processing suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
